        <p>Builds your Wafis project for production, optimizing performance.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <code>wafis new component --name MyComponent</code>
        <p>Adds a new component named 'MyComponent' to your project.</p>
    </div>
</section>
<section>
    <h4>WebAssembly Integration and Future Directions</h4>
    <p>
        A key feature of Wafis is its ongoing integration of WebAssembly using multiple programming languages like C++, Rust, and AssemblyScript. Currently, the framework has successfully integrated AssemblyScript, and efforts are ongoing to enhance this integration in project builds. The planned integration of C++ through Emscripten will also include an automated installation feature for both Windows and Linux systems, which will simplify the inclusion of C++ dependencies into projects.

        In summary, Wafis represents a forward-thinking framework that combines the strengths of React TSX components and WebAssembly to offer robust web development capabilities. While still in pre-alpha, its development path is clearly laid out, promising a rich set of features that will empower developers to build advanced, efficient web applications.
    </p>
</section>
